Package ca.openosp

Class OscarProperties

java.lang.Object
java.util.Dictionary<Object,Object>
java.util.Hashtable<Object,Object>
java.util.Properties
ca.openosp.OscarProperties
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<Object,Object>
public class OscarProperties extends Properties
This class will hold OSCAR invalid input: '&' CAISI properties. It is a singleton class. Do not instantiate it, use the method getInstance(). Every time the properties file changes, tomcat must be restarted.

    • saveProperty

      public void saveProperty(String propFilePath, String key, String value) throws IOException
      Saves property to the specified properties file. This method appends the new property to the end of the file. Updates the in-memory reference of the properties.
      Parameters:
      propFilePath - The path to the properties file.
      key - The key of the property to be saved.
      value - The value of the property to be saved.
      Throws:
      IOException - If an I/O error occurs while writing to the file.
